argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I noticed <strong>Benny Blanco</strong> was at =
the <strong>Clive
Davis</strong> pre-Grammy party without fianc=C3=A9 <strong>Selena Gomez</s=
trong> on Saturday night. Gomez might have been busy, or she didn=E2=80=99t=
 want to get asked about her emotional immigration video, which has become =
a target of the <strong>Trump</strong> White House. But I=E2=80=99m also gu=
essing we won=E2=80=99t see as much of Gomez, <strong>Zoe Salda=C3=B1a</str=
ong>, and the rest of the <em>Emilia P=C3=A9rez</em> talent during the so-c=
alled =E2=80=9CPhase 2=E2=80=9D of Oscar campaigning, which runs from now t=
hrough February 18.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Netflix dodged my questions about p=
lans for the campaign, which is scheduled to rev back up with this weekend=
=E2=80=99s DGA Awards, PGA Awards, and Critics Choice Awards, all of which =
will showcase <em>Emilia P=C3=A9rez</em>. I=E2=80=99m betting the talent wi=
ll show up but do limited, if any, press. All except for Gasc=C3=B3n, who a=
 Netflix source confirms has =E2=80=9Cgone rogue=E2=80=9D with her half-apo=
logy tour on social media and CNN en Espa=C3=B1ol.
She seems to be sticking with a combo of =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m the real vict=
im here=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CAnyone who knows me knows that I am not racis=
t.=E2=80=9D Neither Netflix nor Gasc=C3=B3n=E2=80=99s agency, UTA, nor her =
publicists at The Lede Co. are guiding this strategy, I=E2=80=99m told. Yik=
es.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Everyone in town seems to be shocked that the Netfl=
ix awards team and its leader, <strong>Lisa Taback</strong>, didn=E2=80=99t=
 clean up Gasc=C3=B3n=E2=80=99s social media accounts well
before freelance journalist <strong>Sarah Hagi</strong> either stumbled upo=
n them or was fed them by a rival campaign (or, more likely, a =E2=80=9Csta=
n=E2=80=9D account). But what=E2=80=99s been more surprising to me in conve=
rsations with the top awards consultants is how little vetting of contender=
s happens at <em>any</em> studio or streamer.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">One after=
 another, the strategists told me they rarely go deep on personal accounts
unless there are preexisting red flags. That seems=E2=80=A6 <em>crazy</em> =
in this day and age, with social media increasingly weaponized, and with so=
 much riding on these eight-figure campaigns. These consultants literally a=
gonize over exactly where actors should sit on a guild screening panel, but=
 they don=E2=80=99t look to see if maybe one of them has repeatedly attacke=
d Muslims online? It=E2=80=99s also pretty easy to search their posts for t=
he word =E2=80=9CHitler.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Oscar contenders seem especially vulnerable to t=
he dreaded =E2=80=9Cresurfaced tweet=E2=80=9D because many of them go from =
complete unknowns to semi-ubiquitous media personalities in a matter of mon=
ths. Did anyone know or care about <strong>Lupita Nyong=E2=80=99o</strong> =
or <strong>Eddie Redmayne</strong> or <strong>Charles Melton</strong> or <s=
trong>Jean Dujardin</strong> or <strong>Lucas Hedges</strong> or <strong>Ya=
litza Aparicio</strong> or, say, Karla Sof=C3=ADa Gasc=C3=B3n, until their =
respective
awards campaigns turned them into main characters of the celebrity industri=
al complex? No, so it=E2=80=99s kinda the responsibility of those campaigns=
 to prepare and protect these people=E2=80=A6 even from themselves.<br/><br=
/>Back in 2016, when Fox Searchlight paid a then-record $17.5 million for <=
em>The Birth of a Nation</em>, information about filmmaker <strong>Nate Par=
ker</strong>=E2=80=99s college rape trial was just sitting on his Wikipedia=
 page for anyone to see. After those resurfaced allegations derailed the
movie, I remember a lot of =E2=80=9Cnever again=E2=80=9D hand-wringing abou=
t vetting key talent before jumping into bed with them. Seems everyone forg=
ot. Maybe now they=E2=80=99ll remember. =C2=A0</p></div>
