rong> and <strong>Leslie Sloane</strong>) and the need to recoup hundreds o=
f millions of dollars in damages ASAP. =E2=80=9CYes, that=E2=80=99s why you=
 sued, I get it,=E2=80=9D retorted Liman.<br/><br/>What about those not ins=
ide the courtroom, like <em>The New York Times</em>, which hasn=E2=80=99t b=
een served yet? Surely,
the <em>Times</em> will want to protect its source discussions. I could see=
 the paper filing motions on this front. If the litigation indeed devolves =
